FBIS4-58556 "drnes087_v_94007" FBIS-NES-94-087 Daily Report 4 May 1994 Pakistan Government To End Public Execution of Criminals Government To End Public Execution of Criminals BK0405160294 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 1400 GMT 4 May 94 BK0405160294 Islamabad PTV Television Network English BFN [Text] The government has decided as a matter of policy not to carry out executions of criminals sentenced to death in public despite the powers vested in it to do so under Section 10 of the Special Courts for Speedy Trials Act 1992. The present government respects the human dignity and upholds the human values as upheld by the civilized and progressive societies of the world.
